sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36725
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The mmoXYBZDC gene cluster is a methane monooxygenase found in methylococcus capsulatus. It catalyzes a C-H bond in methane, converting it to methanol.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The whole mmoXYBZDC gene cluster needs to work together to create the desired methane monooxygenase function.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tammy Hsu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 5' Bicistronic UTR (strong), does not include ATG start
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: c/o Vivek Mutalik et al. BIOFAB Emeryville
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: 5' UTR based on bicistronic junction architecture. First RBS is strong and drives expression of short leader cistron. Second RBS internal to first cistron control translation of gene of interest. Architecture is optimized so that downstream CDS for gene of interest does not have a chance to form a secondary structure with the 5' UTR. See BIOFAB.org for more information.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36715
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: mmoX (methane monooxygenase subunit A, alpha chain)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: mmoX is part of a methane monooxygenase complex (subunit A, alpha chain). It helps oxidize a C-H bond in methane, converting it to methanol.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: mmoX needs the other mmo genes for the methane monooxygenase function.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tammy Hsu
